column28: severe headache, fatigue, dizziness, shortness of breath
column32: Persistent headache with dizziness and breathlessness are common in uncontrolled high blood pressure.
column33: Check blood pressure immediately. Seek urgent care if shortness of breath worsens.

column28: fever, cough, sore throat, runny nose
column32: Flu typically presents with fever, cough, sore throat, and runny nose.
column33: Stay hydrated, rest, and take fever reducers. See a doctor if symptoms last more than a week.

column28: chest pain, fatigue, palpitations, shortness of breath
column32: Chest pain and palpitations with breathlessness often indicate reduced blood flow to the heart.
column33: Seek emergency care immediately. Do not ignore chest pain.

column32: Abdominal pain with diarrhea and bloating suggests viral or bacterial gastroenteritis.
column33: Drink plenty of fluids to avoid dehydration. See a doctor if diarrhea persists >3 days.

column28: weight loss, frequent urination, excessive thirst, fatigue
column32: Chronic fatigue with excessive thirst, urination, and weight loss is typical in diabetes.
column33: Schedule a medical check-up and blood sugar test. Long-term management required.
